From 1c113f79f6ad9c6a2f943ea7e5f82f81de98b739 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 12:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] include cstdint for drm tip helper

Fixes compile failure where fixed-width integer types are used without
including <cstdint> in drm_tip_helper.cpp.

This is only required on the pinned releases/25.48 branch. Upstream
removed this file entirely when deprecating DG1 support, so there is no
upstream change to submit:
  873fbd09c38dba9416b62526fa601d1ffe480142
  ("refactor: Remove deprecated code for DG1")

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [file removed upstream in 873fbd09c38d; needed only on releases/25.48]

Signed-off-by: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
---
 .../source/os_interface/linux/local/dg1/drm_tip_helper.cpp     | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

Index: intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8/shared/source/os_interface/linux/local/dg1/drm_tip_helper.cpp
===================================================================
--- intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8.orig/shared/source/os_interface/linux/local/dg1/drm_tip_helper.cpp
+++ intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8/shared/source/os_interface/linux/local/dg1/drm_tip_helper.cpp
@@ -10,1 +10,2 @@
-#include <memory>
+#include <cstdint>
+#include <memory>

